body_html:
If this isn't a bug, it will be better/faster answered on StackOverflow — the correct place to ask for help.

If this is a bug, please follow guidelines for reporting problems. When you click on "New issue" there is a template to be filled. It is very hard to reproduce your problem and check what's wrong if you don't provide the required information. For example, you did not provide a sample code for reproducing the problem. ;-)

Looking just at your error message, I would say your input vector is wrongly formatted. Try printing it to see what's going on.

body:
If this isn't a bug, it will be better/faster answered on [StackOverflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tensorflow) — the correct place to ask for help.

If this is a bug, please follow guidelines for reporting problems. When you click on "New issue" there is a template to be filled. It is very hard to reproduce your problem and check what's wrong if you don't provide the required information. For example, you did not provide a sample code for reproducing the problem. ;-)

Looking just at your error message, I would say your input vector is wrongly formatted. Try printing it to see what's going on.
